caption: Went to Chinatown for an afternoon treat and ended up bringing food from this place to try at home for dinner time. Let me tell you, it was a great decision. My kids really enjoyed the regular crispy chicken strips and not to mention the exploding flavor of the spicy wings! We also got some Korean beef tacos (sliced beef, coleslaw mixture, chipotle-like mayo on a flour tortilla) and they were surprisingly delicious! It was an awesome food experience overall and would definitely recommend. We will be going back for the “Soy Garlic” flavor chicken strips! Only got 1 piece to try and we all LOVED it!

If you are looking for Korean chicken wings for delivery, this is a fantastic option. I first ate at this restaurant pre-COVID and it became my #1 favorite place for spicy Korean chicken wings. Post-COVID, even with delivery, it still delivers (pun intended) on the flavor.  The meals are well-packaged in strong containers.  None of that weak-sauce packaging here. I asked for utensils and was pleasantly surprised to see forks, chopsticks, and plenty of napkins.  *PRO TIP: if you are ordering through the app (or phone, etc), ask for extra plates! We ate out of the containers, which isn’t a big deal, but since we were staying at a hotel, it would’ve been clutch to have some extra plates to eat from.  The food itself came surprisingly hot and the wings were still crunchy. Admittedly, it’s not the exact magic that occurs when you dine in, but that’s to be expected. It’s a strong offering for delivery.  By the way, I LOVE spicy foods and see myself as being able to handle the spice well. These spicy wings are pretty spicy. Not the spiciest ever, but it makes you think you maybe order an “extra spicy” version or something. It’s VERY flavorful and delicious, but just be warned: it’s spicy.  In short, if you are craving some Korean chicken wings for delivery (or any Korean cuisine for that matter) Bonchon prepares the food quickly, packages it well, and the flavors are well-preserved compared to its in-person offering. Although I would prefer to dine-in, I also wouldn’t hesitate to order delivery again when the craving strikes.

This was my first time at Bon Chon. I was excited to try it because I heard the sauce here is really good and I love Korean fried chicken. People aren't wrong, the sauce was really good and the wings were fried well, but the price and the size of the wings was very disappointing. The crunch of the wings and sauce was delicious, but the size and value of the wings were horrible. I would come back, just for the sauce and the style of fried chicken, but the price and size definitely disappointed. We got the small wings, which comes with about 10 wings and a small bowl of daikon, for $13 plus tip. I think you can get cheaper wings and just as good, somewhere else. Staff was nice, but very inattentive; it took a while for service and for acknowledgement. We had to flag down staff a couple times to put in our order and to get our check. There's not a lot of seating in this restaurant and it was business the night we came in. I love Korean fried chicken, but I don't think this was a great experience, not did we get value for our dollar. I recommend trying the soy garlic sauce, if you do come because it was a bit sweet and salty. I had high expectations coming into the restaurant, which probably ruined it for me. The restaurant was busy when we came in. There's no WiFi, there's a bathroom in the back, and limited seating. Staff was friendly, but seemed busy and uncaring.

I think this Bonchon chain beats out many of the other Korean fried chicken places in Chicago, including Crisp, Del Seoul, En Hakkore 2.0, and Tteok.  We always go for the wings, sometimes drumsticks, with the spicy and soy-glazed sauces. We tried the sweet crunch last night too, and this was very sweet. I liked it but I don’t think it’s for everyone. What I do love is how the wings always come out piping hot and super crispy.  The other entree/side dishes are just okay and I wouldn’t really recommend them. The pickled radishes are a nice side but usually not vinegary enough. The coleslaw is on the soggy side with way too much mayo. The drinks/soju are pretty straightforward but there’s quite an upcharge. Overall, the prices are very reasonable and the service is nice and fast.  PS. The spicy wings are quiteee spicy. I’m generally okay with my spice and these really hit the spot if you’re craving something HOT.

Went with the medium combo half and half - soy garlic and sweet crunch. The soy garlic is by far my favorite! I was just a little disappointed at how small the drum sticks were. Keep in mind, that the medium combo includes 15 pieces for $24.75. 10 wings + 5 drum stick. If you look at the picture below, that’s how big the drumsticks were compared to the wings.  Service was also slow. We couldn’t find our server half the time (restaurant is also not that big) and we would wait and wait until we flagged the next server to get our check.  It was good experience overall, would come again, but would recommend other places before bon chon.
